{
  "text": "Mayor et al. [CITATION_1] reported that almost half of the human adult population from Manhica town were positive for P. falciparum during the dry season, and that rates may be even higher in the wet season. Mabunda et al. [CITATION_2] reported human malaria parasite prevalence of 58.9% of which 52.4% were due to P. falciparum, the burden being in the northern areas and also the coastal areas, where Maragra is situated. The high sporozoite rates found in An. funestus in this study would support findings on high levels of parasitaemia in the human populations.",
